                </div>
                
                <div class="news-description">
                    <div class="news-id">heic1707 — Photo Release</div>
                    <div class="news-title">Search for stellar survivor of a supernova explosion</div>
                    <div class="news-teaser"><strong>30 March 2017</strong>: Astronomers have used the NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope to observe the remnant of a supernova explosion in the Large Magellanic Cloud. Beyond just delivering a beautiful image, Hubble may well have traced the surviving remains of the exploded star’s companion.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="news-readmore">Read more</div>
            </div> <!-- news-wrapper -->
        </a>
