                    <div class="news-id">heic1704 — Photo Release</div>
                    <div class="news-title">Cosmic blast from the past</div>
                    <div class="news-teaser"><strong>24 February 2017</strong>: Three decades ago, a massive stellar explosion sent shockwaves not only through space but also through the astronomical community. SN 1987A was the closest observed supernova to Earth since the invention of the telescope and has become by far the best studied of all time, revolutionising our understanding of the explosive death of massive stars.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="news-readmore">Read more</div>
